menu "LKCAMP educational drivers"

config EDU_PBUF
	tristate "Educational pseudo buffer character driver"
	default m
	help
	  Builds /dev/edu_pbuf, an educational pseudo character driver
	  based on the LKCAMP device-driver tutorial.

	  The driver stores bytes written by user space in a kernel buffer,
	  returns them through read(), and exposes ioctl commands to query,
	  clear, and configure the logical write limit of the buffer.

	  To build it as a module, choose M. The module will be called
	  edu_pbuf.

endmenu
